CB027 Bonum est confidere, f. 100v

fields.notes:
Origin: France ?
Bifolio with music pieces added to an incomplete copy of the Historia scholastica by Petrus Comestor, chancellor of Notre-Dame of Paris in the 1160s. Contains four monophonic conducti and one two-part motet, all belonging to the Notre-Dame repertoire. Most of the texts have medieval attribution to Philippe the Chancellor (d. 1236) in other sources. The manuscript does not seem to have originated in Spain. In fact, both handwritings do not display Spanish features and are rather closer to French scripts of the 13th century.
See description in https://www.diamm.ac.uk/sources/3967/#/
Bevilacque:  "messine neumes". Note CC: ?? The axis of the notation and the shapes of the neumes are not at all lotharingian.
